## ğŸ§  How a Rep is Validated

Helify uses biomechanical rules.

### Range of Motion (ROM)

| Rule | Value |
|------|------|
| Start / End Position | â‰¥ 165Â° |
| Minimum Depth | â‰¤ 110Â° |
| Hyper-extension Warning | > 175Â° |

If the knee does not bend enough:


âš ï¸ Increase range


If the knee extends too far:


â— Do not overextend


---

### Speed Rules

| Condition | Time |
|--------|------|
| Too Fast (momentum) | < 2.0 seconds |
| Ideal | 2.0 â€“ 4.0 seconds |
| Too Slow | > 6.0 seconds |

Feedback examples:
- **Slow down**
- **Maintain steady pace**

